ture. It documents how conservation efforts are transformed through the political economy of platforms and the algorithmic feeds that have been instrumental to the rise of post-truth politics. Developing a novel account of post-truth as an expression of power under platform capitalism, Bram Büscher shows how environmental actors attempt to mediate between structural forms of platform power and the contingent histories and contexts of particular environmental issues. Bringing efforts at wildlife protection in Southern Africa into dialogue with a sweeping analysis of truth and power in the twenty-first century, Büscher makes the case for a new environmental politics that radically reignites the art of speaking truth to power.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 0aConservation of natural resourcesxPolitical aspects. 0aEnvironmental protectionxPolitical aspects. 0aEnvironmentalismxPolitical aspects. 0aWildlife conservationzAfrica, Southern. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520976153zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520976153423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520976153.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Engli